<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Sumpix | Home</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/globals.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="hamburger">
      <div class="line"></div>
      <div class="line"></div>
      <div class="line"></div>
    </div>

    <nav class="flex justify-between px-10 py-8 navbar">
      <div class="navbar-left flex gap-6">
        <div class="navbar-brand">
          <img src="/assets/logo.webp" alt="" width="55" height="55" />
        </div>
        <ul class="list flex gap-5">
          <li><a href="https://sumpix0.vercel.app/">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://sumpix0.vercel.app#features">Features</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/demss233">Github</a></li>
          <li><a href="mailto:shivsatyam86@gmail.com">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="navbar-right">
        <button
          class="button-pink-filled"
          onclick="window.location.href=`https://sumpix0.vercel.app/create`"
        >
          Get Started
        </button>
      </div>
    </nav>
    <div class="container w-[93%] flex flex-col items-center gap-60">
      <div class="hero w-fit text-center flex flex-col gap-5">
        <h1 class="text-white text-3xl sm:text-4xl">
          Make note-taking a breeze with Sumpix! Fast, efficient, and totally
          modern. ðŸ‘‹
        </h1>
        <p class="text-[#b6b5b2]">
          Effortlessly summarize your notes with Sumpix! âœ¨ Make 'em pop and
          share with anyone you please. Best of luck on your future endeavors!
        </p>
        <div class="buttons flex gap-4 w-fit mx-auto mt-6">
          <button
            class="button-pink-filled"
            onclick="window.location.href='https://sumpix0.vercel.app/create'"
          >
            Get Started
          </button>
          <button
            class="button-pink-outlined"
            onclick="window.open('https://github.com/demss233')"
          >
            Github
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="features flex flex-col gap-40">
        <div
          class="card flex flex-col sm:flex-row w-[100%] justify-evenly items-center"
        >
          <div class="card-img">
            <img
              src="/assets/card-one.webp"
              alt=""
              width="300px"
              height="400px"
            />
          </div>
          <div
            class="card-details w-[90%] mt-6 sm:mt-0 sm:w-[60%] flex flex-col gap-4"
          >
            <div class="card-heading">
              <h1 class="text-white text-3xl" id="features">
                Summarise With Ease
              </h1>
            </div>
            <div class="card-text">
              <p class="text-[#b6b5b2]">
                Efficiently and quickly summarise any data and reduce the amount
                of work you do. We are currently relying on a node module for
                text summarisation. Make sure to give Sumpix a try and the
                <a
                  href="https://github.com/SwapnikKatkoori/node-summarizer"
                  class="text-[#cb0ced]"
                  >Github</a
                >
                repository of the node module. You can also choose how many
                useful sentences you want from the provided paragaph.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="card flex flex-col sm:flex-row-reverse w-[100%] justify-evenly items-center flex-row-reverse"
        >
          <div class="card-img">
            <img
              src="/assets/card-two.webp"
              alt=""
              width="300px"
              height="400px"
            />
          </div>
          <div
            class="card-details w-[90%] mt-6 sm:mt-0 sm:w-[60%] flex flex-col gap-4"
          >
            <div class="card-heading">
              <h1 class="text-white text-3xl">Add visuals to your summary</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="card-text">
              <p class="text-[#b6b5b2]">
                You can add high quality and trusted images in your summaries
                based on the keywords you provide. We are currently relying on
                Unsplash for this service. The API is well built and easy to
                use. We will surely suggest you to check out unsplash. You are
                supposed to provide reasonable and correct keywords. Writing
                vulgar keywords is strictly prohibited.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="card flex flex-col sm:flex-row w-[100%] justify-evenly items-center"
        >
          <div class="card-img">
            <img
              src="/assets/card-three.webp"
              alt=""
              width="300px"
              height="400px"
            />
          </div>
          <div
            class="card-details w-[90%] mt-6 sm:mt-0 sm:w-[60%] flex flex-col gap-4"
          >
            <div class="card-heading">
              <h1 class="text-white text-3xl">Share and enlighten.</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="card-text">
              <p class="text-[#b6b5b2]">
                The best part is that you can easily share these notes with your
                friends and enlighten them. These short and sharp summaries will
                also help them. We are currently using MongoDB Atlas to store
                data because it is fast, certified and easy to use.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div
      class="footer bg-[#1c1c1c] w-[100%] mt-60 p-10 flex flex-col gap-4 justify-center items-center"
    >
      <div class="footer-heading">
        <h1 class="text-white text-3xl font-semibold">Questions ?</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-details">
        <p class="text-[#b6b5b2]">
          If there is something you want to tell us. You can Contact
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-buttons flex gap-4 mt-6">
        <button class="button-pink-filled">Github</button>
        <button class="button-pink-outlined">Discord</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <script src="/scripts/navbar.js">
      for(let pointer = 0; pointer < 3; ++pointer) {
        window.location.reload();
      }
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
